org.stekikun.dolmen.cli

Class Args

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.stekikun.dolmen.cli.Args

  • public final class Args
extends Object
    This class describes the various command-line arguments that can be used with the Dolmen CLI as an enumeration. This enumerations drives a generic command-line parsing implementation which is used by the CLI in Dolmen.

      • parse

        public static Args parse(String[] args)
                  throws Args.ArgsParsingException
        Parses the given array of command-line arguments args according to the various available options described in Args.Item.

        The expected format of the command-line arguments is as follows:

        • options are introduced with a double hyphen -- followed by their name, e.g. --name
        • options may be available with a one-character short name as well, in which case they are introduced with a single hyphen, e.g. -n
        • when an option expects a value of some type, the value must directly follow the option in the argument array; flag options require no value
        • it is possible to use the short name notation to give more than one option at a time, e.g. -lah, provided all given options are flags
        • stray arguments which are not associated to an option are taken as is and put in an extra arguments list.
        Parameters:
        args -
        Returns:
        an instance of Args which contains the result of the parsing of args
        Throws:
        Args.ArgsParsingException - if an error is encountered while parsing args
        See Also:
        getFlag(Item), getNumeric(Item), getString(Item), getExtras()
